8:
Hey, any of those worlds you guys
visit feature a black hole? That'd
make the BEST escape room.
11: No, and uh... when did you get here?
15:
Ugh, a real stickler for details, huh?
You should consider a career in
sugar sculpture.
18:
Guess I've got some 'splaining to
do... It all started when I was still a
sushi chef on my home planet,
Golgol...
22:
Before we get too invested, this is all
a lie, right?
26:
Huh? 'Course it is. I am but a mere
Umamusume from Tracen
Academy.
30:
Truth is, I've got a race next week,
but I can't work up the motivation to
train.
36:
N-now hold on a minute. I thought
races were of the utmost
importance to Umamusume?!
40:
Oh, they are. They're as important to
us as the garnish is to sushi.
50: All right, let's go somewhere fun.
54:
I know just the place. The
atmosphere is perfect for relaxing,
and the weather should be perfect.
60:
Oho, now we're gettin' somewhere!
You really know how to treat an
Umamusume right!
64:
With that, I dub thee... the Golshi
Expedition Team! Now, WE'RE OFF
FOR ADVENTUUURE!
72:
I do not know, but I suppose we shall
find out.
82:
WHOOOAAA! Trees as far as the eye
can see! Gigantic bees! DANCING
MUSHROOMS!
86:
Nice job, Stella! I can really tell I'm in
a whole new world! I'm ALMOST at a
lost for words!
94:
She seems satisfied, but with the
way she's acting, she may never
want to leave.
98:
W-well, I'm sure after she's had her
fill here, she'll want to do something
else.
101:
When that time comes, we'll just get
her attention back on racing and—
121: Uh... Do I even want to ask?
139:
I finally understand... The truth of the
universe lies just beyond those
rainbow donut holes.
148:
Pretty nice fella, that one. Really
cheered me up.
151:
Although, for all I know, he could've
been cursing me out the whole time.
156:
Shall we go ask Challua to interpret
for us?
160:
Nah... I don't want to betray my new
comrade's trust. That mushroom
and I are one in heart now!
163:
Yeah, that's it. We're tight like
elephants and orcas.
170:
And so, having been accepted by
the locals, the Golshi Expedition
Team heads further into the dense
forest.
174:
Well, what're ya waitin' for?! It's
training time! Last one there's a
rotten egg!
185:
Maaan, that was fun! You're a real
speedster, Alk! You even kept up
with the great and powerful Golshi!
189:
Ohoho... For your efforts, I shall now
present you with a reward.
197:
The legendary sword Sticky. 'Tis the
perfect size for preschoolers to play
swords with.
201:
Hey, uh... Is it okay for you to be
slacking off like this?
205:
This again? You're a real advocate
for the daily grind of modern
society, aren't ya?
209:
Listen, the racecourse is like the
battlefield to us Umamusume. That
makes us warriors, yeah? And
warriors need rest too, right?
212:
No matter what they're like off the
track, all Umamusume turn into
fighting machines when it's time for
a race.
216:
There's no better feeling than giving
your all during a race. It's like your
whole body's on fire!
220: It sounds like you enjoy racing.
230:
Oooh, I get it now. This is your
pre-race routine, right?
233:
You've got a long and hard battle
ahead of you, so you're just taking
the time to relax beforehand.
237:
That's it, all right. I've gotta center
myself—hear the voice of the
beetles scurrying about, the rustling
of leaves...
240:
...As I feel my frustration gauge
suddenly spike!
253:
Enough of this nature business! My
heart screams for battle!
257:
Get up, everyone, we're headed
home! I can't wait one yoctosecond
more!
265:
The racecourse is calling me! Let's
go!
